# Auto-deploy after changes

After completing any code change in this repo, deploy it live without waiting for the user to ask.

## Workflow

1. Verify the change builds (`npm run build` or `npm run build:pages` when relevant).
2. Commit only the files changed for the task with a concise message.
3. Push to `main` (GitHub Pages deploys from `main` via `.github/workflows/deploy-pages.yml`).
4. Wait for the `Deploy to GitHub Pages` workflow to finish successfully.
5. Tell the user the live URL to check (usually `https://moazzamitr-bit.github.io/ooj/...`).

## Notes

- Do not ask the user to deploy manually unless push or CI fails.
- Mention hard refresh (`Cmd+Shift+R`) if they may see a cached page.
- Use `/Users/moazzami/.local/bin/gh` if `gh` is not on PATH.
